# Progress Tracker Context

Before making any code changes or starting any task, read `PROGRESS_TRACKER.md` in the project root to understand:

- What has already been completed
- What is currently pending
- The current connection details (VM IP, port, database, credentials)
- The folder structure and package decisions already made

## When to read it

- At the start of every new task or conversation
- Before adding new packages or files (to avoid duplicating work)
- Before changing connection settings or credentials

## When to update it

- After completing any meaningful step (see `update-progress.mdc` for details)
- Mark items `[x]` as they are completed
- Add new pending items when they are discovered
- Keep **Connection Details** table current if anything changes
